Note:
Comprehensive tests for the OS module
:End Note

Note: Test basic directory operations
:End Note

Let cwd be get current working directory
Assert length of cwd is greater than 0

Let test_dir be "test_os_directory"
Create directory test_dir
Assert is directory at test_dir is equal to true

Let nested_dir be "test_os_directory/nested/subdir"
Create directories nested_dir
Assert is directory at nested_dir is equal to true

Note: Test directory listing
:End Note
Let files be list directory at path test_dir
Assert length of files is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test file operations
:End Note
Let test_file be "test_os_directory/test_file.txt"
Write "Test content" to file test_file
Assert file test_file exists is equal to true

Let copy_file be "test_os_directory/copied_file.txt"
Copy file from test_file to copy_file
Assert file copy_file exists is equal to true

Let move_file be "test_os_directory/moved_file.txt"
Move file from copy_file to move_file
Assert file move_file exists is equal to true
Assert file copy_file exists is equal to false

Note: Test file information
:End Note
Let file_size be size of file test_file
Assert file_size is greater than 0

Let permissions be file permissions of test_file
Assert permissions is greater than 0

Let owner be owner of file test_file
Assert length of owner is greater than 0

Let modified_time be last modified time of file test_file
Assert modified_time is greater than 0

Note: Test file type checks
:End Note
Assert is file at test_file is equal to true
Assert is directory at test_file is equal to false
Assert is directory at test_dir is equal to true
Assert is file at test_dir is equal to false

Note: Test path operations
:End Note
Let abs_path be absolute path of test_file
Assert length of abs_path is greater than 0

Let joined_path be join paths ["folder", "subfolder", "file.txt"]
Assert length of joined_path is greater than 0

Let path_parts be split path "/home/user/documents/file.txt"
Assert length of path_parts is greater than 0

Let ext be file extension of "document.pdf"
Assert ext is equal to "pdf"

Let filename be filename of "/path/to/file.txt"
Assert filename is equal to "file.txt"

Let dirname be directory of "/path/to/file.txt"
Assert dirname is equal to "/path/to"

Note: Test system directories
:End Note
Let temp_dir be system temporary directory
Assert length of temp_dir is greater than 0

Let home_dir be user home directory
Assert length of home_dir is greater than 0

Let system_dir be system directory
Assert length of system_dir is greater than 0

Let user_dir be user directory
Assert length of user_dir is greater than 0

Note: Test temporary file creation
:End Note
Let temp_file be create temp file with prefix as "runa_test_" and suffix as ".tmp"
Assert file temp_file exists is equal to true
Write "Temporary content" to file temp_file
Delete file temp_file

Let temp_dir be create temp directory with prefix as "runa_test_"
Assert is directory at temp_dir is equal to true
Delete file temp_dir

Note: Test environment variables
:End Note
Let path_var be get environment variable "PATH"
Assert length of path_var is greater than 0

Set environment variable "TEST_VAR" to "test_value"
Let test_var be get environment variable "TEST_VAR"
Assert test_var is equal to "test_value"

Unset environment variable "TEST_VAR"
Let test_var_after be get environment variable "TEST_VAR"
Assert test_var_after is equal to ""

Let all_env_vars be get all environment variables
Assert length of all_env_vars is greater than 0

Note: Test process information
:End Note
Let process_id be get current process id
Assert process_id is greater than 0

Let parent_id be get parent process id
Assert parent_id is greater than 0

Let process_name be get process name
Assert length of process_name is greater than 0

Let process_cwd be get process working directory
Assert length of process_cwd is greater than 0

Note: Test command execution
:End Note
Let result be execute command "echo Hello World"
Assert result["exit_code"] is equal to 0
Assert result["output"] contains "Hello World"

Let result_with_args be execute command with args "echo" and ["Hello", "Runa"]
Assert result_with_args["exit_code"] is equal to 0
Assert result_with_args["output"] contains "Hello Runa"

Note: Test system information
:End Note
Let platform be get system platform
Assert length of platform is greater than 0

Let architecture be get system architecture
Assert length of architecture is greater than 0

Let version be get system version
Assert length of version is greater than 0

Let system_name be get system name
Assert length of system_name is greater than 0

Let system_info be get system info
Assert length of system_info is greater than 0

Note: Test hardware information
:End Note
Let cpu_count be get cpu count
Assert cpu_count is greater than 0

Let cpu_usage be get cpu usage
Assert cpu_usage is greater than or equal to 0
Assert cpu_usage is less than or equal to 100

Let memory_info be get memory info
Assert memory_info["total"] is greater than 0
Assert memory_info["available"] is greater than 0
Assert memory_info["used"] is greater than or equal to 0

Let disk_info be get disk info "/"
Assert disk_info["total"] is greater than 0
Assert disk_info["free"] is greater than 0
Assert disk_info["used"] is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test network information
:End Note
Let interfaces be get network interfaces
Assert length of interfaces is greater than 0

Let hostname be get hostname
Assert length of hostname is greater than 0

Note: Test user information
:End Note
Let username be get username
Assert length of username is greater than 0

Let user_id be get user id
Assert user_id is greater than 0

Let group_id be get group id
Assert group_id is greater than 0

Let user_groups be get user groups
Assert length of user_groups is greater than 0

Let is_admin_val be is admin
Assert is_admin_val is a boolean

Note: Test system monitoring
:End Note
Let uptime be get system uptime
Assert uptime is greater than 0

Let boot_time be get system boot time
Assert boot_time is greater than 0

Let load_averages be get system load
Assert length of load_averages is greater than 0

Let system_health be get system health
Assert length of system_health is greater than 0

Let system_security be get system security
Assert length of system_security is greater than 0

Let metrics be get system metrics
Assert length of metrics is greater than 0

Note: Test system services
:End Note
Let services be get system services
Assert length of services is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system logs
:End Note
Let system_logs be get system logs "system"
Assert length of system_logs is greater than or equal to 0

Write system log "Test log message" with level as "info"

Note: Test system events and alerts
:End Note
Let system_events be get system events
Assert length of system_events is greater than or equal to 0

Let alerts be get system alerts
Assert length of alerts is greater than or equal to 0

Set system alert for "cpu_usage" with threshold as 80
Set system alert for "memory_usage" with threshold as 90

Note: Test notifications
:End Note
Let notifications be get system notifications
Assert length of notifications is greater than or equal to 0

Send system notification with title as "Test Notification" and message as "This is a test"

Note: Test system packages
:End Note
Let packages be get system packages
Assert length of packages is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system updates
:End Note
Let updates be get system updates
Assert length of updates is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system drivers and devices
:End Note
Let drivers be get system drivers
Assert length of drivers is greater than or equal to 0

Let devices be get system devices
Assert length of devices is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system volumes
:End Note
Let volumes be get system volumes
Assert length of volumes is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system users and groups
:End Note
Let system_users be get system users
Assert length of system_users is greater than or equal to 0

Let system_groups be get system groups
Assert length of system_groups is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test scheduled tasks
:End Note
Let scheduled_tasks be get system scheduled tasks
Assert length of scheduled_tasks is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system backups
:End Note
Let backups be get system backups
Assert length of backups is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test system monitoring
:End Note
Set system monitoring to true
Let monitoring_data be get system monitoring
Assert length of monitoring_data is greater than or equal to 0

Note: Test error handling
:End Note
Try:
    Let result be execute command "nonexistent_command_that_should_fail"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for non-existent command
    :End Note

Try:
    Create directory "/invalid/path/that/should/fail"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for invalid path
    :End Note

Note: Test file removal
:End Note
Remove file test_file
Assert file test_file exists is equal to false

Remove recursive test_dir
Assert is directory at test_dir is equal to false

Note: Test process management
:End Note
Let bg_process_id be execute command background "sleep 1"
Assert bg_process_id is greater than 0

If is process running bg_process_id:
    Call print with message as "Background process is running"
    Kill process bg_process_id
    Let exit_code be wait for process bg_process_id
    Call print with message as "Process exited with code: " plus exit_code

Note: Test process information
:End Note
Let process_info be get process info process_id
Assert length of process_info is greater than 0

Let all_processes be get all processes
Assert length of all_processes is greater than 0

Note: Test complex OS workflow
:End Note
Let workflow_dir be "os_workflow_test"
Create directory workflow_dir

Let test_files be ["file1.txt", "file2.txt", "file3.txt"]
For each filename in test_files:
    Let file_path be join paths [workflow_dir, filename]
    Write "Content for " plus filename to file file_path
    Assert file file_path exists is equal to true

Let workflow_files be list directory at path workflow_dir
Assert length of workflow_files is equal to 3

For each file in workflow_files:
    Let file_path be join paths [workflow_dir, file]
    Let file_size be size of file file_path
    Assert file_size is greater than 0

Remove recursive workflow_dir
Assert is directory at workflow_dir is equal to false

Call print with message as "All OS module tests passed!" 